{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01E4VZcPYKNUSFyPaQivGuH3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The ConfigMap `config-audit` is created with 11,208 bytes of findings. Here's a summary of what the audit found:\n\n**4 FAILs (critical):**\n1. **No audit logging** — `xpack.security.audit.enabled` is absent on all nodes; no record of access or privileged operations (SOC2/PCI-DSS/HIPAA gap)\n2. **No Kubernetes NetworkPolicies** — any pod in the cluster can reach ports 9200/9300; authentication is the only gate\n3. **Snapshot repo uses plain HTTP** — backup traffic to MinIO is unencrypted; credentials and data are exposed on the pod network\n4. **No SLM snapshot policy** — the MinIO repo exists but no automated snapshot schedule is configured; no guaranteed recovery point\n\n**8 WARNings (medium):**\n- Stale credential secret (`elastic-password-next` is active but `elastic-password` still exists, causing the `auth-checker` readiness probe to fail)\n- `bootstrap.memory_lock=false` — heap can be paged to disk swap, risking data exposure\n- Deprecated `kibana` user still enabled\n- No least-privilege application users — only the `elastic` superuser is in practical use\n- Master nodes (es-0/1/2) also serve data/ingest/ml roles — master instability risk under I/O load\n- `action.auto_create_index=true` with no restriction list\n- `app-data` index has single-zone shard routing (`zone=new`) with no fallback\n- HTTP compression disabled\n\n**Passed:** TLS on HTTP and transport layers, authentication required with no anonymous access, destructive ops require name, no active API keys, no custom/unknown user accounts, internal ClusterIP service exposure only."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":203,"cache_read_input_tokens":56710,"output_tokens":418,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier